{
    "id": "337",
    "title": "Injury Severity Score (ISS)",
    "desc": "The Injury Severity Score (ISS) Standardizes severity of traumatic injury based on worst injury of 6 body systems.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/4814394",
                "text": "Baker SP, O'Neill B, Haddon W Jr, Long WB. The injury severity score: a method for describing patients with multiple injuries and evaluating emergency care. J Trauma. 1974 Mar;14(3):187-96. PubMed PMID: 4814394."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/5107365",
                "text": "Rating the severity of tissue damage. I. The abbreviated scale. JAMA. 1971;215(2):277-80."
            },
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/965234",
                "text": "Semmlow JL, Cone R. Utility of the injury severity score: a confirmation. Health Serv Res. 1976;11(1):45-52."
            },
            {
                "href": "https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0020138378900049",
                "text": "Bull JP. Measures of severity of injury. Injury. 1978;9(3):184-7."
            },
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3123707",
                "text": "Copes WS, Champion HR, Sacco WJ, Lawnick MM, Keast SL, Bain LW. The Injury Severity Score revisited. J Trauma. 1988;28(1):69-77."
            }
        ],
        "evidence": "<p>Assign an Abbreviated Injury Scale (AIS) Score to the most severe injury in each body system as follows:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Severity</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>AIS</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>No injury</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Minor</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Moderate</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Serious</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Severe</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>4</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Critical</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>5</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Unsurvivable</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>6</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Then, if the 3 most severe injuries in 3 body systems are A, B, and C, then</p>\n<p>ISS = A&sup2; + B&sup2; + C&sup2;</p>\n<p>If a patient has an AIS of 6 in any body system, they are automatically assigned an ISS of 75.</p>",
        "facts": "",
        "estimation": [],
        "primary_complains": [
            "Injury/Trauma"
        ],
        "disease_treated": [
            "Trauma"
        ],
        "logic": "var calc_output=[]; \n\nvar arr=new Array(parseFloat(head_neck),parseFloat(face),parseFloat(chest),parseFloat(abdomen),parseFloat(extremity),parseFloat(external));\nfunction sortNumber(param2,param1){var first=parseFloat(param1);var second=parseFloat(param2);if(first==second)return 0;if(first<second)return-1;else return 1}var arrsort=arr.sort(sortNumber);if(arrsort[0]==6||arrsort[1]==6||arrsort[2]==6){var u=75;var msg='Maximum Injury Severity Score.<br/><br/>Major Trauma Sustained.'}else{var u=arrsort[0]*arrsort[0];u+=arrsort[1]*arrsort[1];u+=arrsort[2]*arrsort[2];var msg='Out of a possible 75 points'} \n\ncalc_output.push({\n    name:'mini',\n    value:u.toFixed(0),\n    value_text:'points',\n    message:'Injury Severity Score'\n}); \ncalc_output.push({\n    name:'1239_Injury Severity Score_result',\n    value:u.toFixed(0),\n    value_text:'points',\n    message:msg\n});",
